description:
Zalika or "Hack" is an African Metahuman who grew up in the Korogocho slum. She worked for a gang in the slum as a hacker and overtime she discovered her powers of teleporting via the internet. After avenging her brother's death, Hack started stealing from large corporations and stealing the money for herself. It got the NSA's attention but instead she ended up in the Temho-Metya Prison when someone named Karla set up a trap for her.

In Suicide Squad #2, the Suicide Squad freed her and agreed to work for them. Hack got them all out from trouble and teleported everyone back to Belle Reve. She is the squad's newest member.

Abilities

Hack has the ability to travel through the internet and download files to her brain. She can easily hack into a system without using any form of gadgetry.

description:
Current Events

Copperhead has appeared in the pages of All-Star Batman, where she shot Batman with a poison arrow in his side in an attempt to collect Two-Face's bounty on him.

Origin

Not yet revealed.

Creation

The character Copperhead was originally created for Batman: Arkham Origins. She made her first appearance in comics of Batman: Arkham Unhinged issue 10, created by Derek Fridolfs and Bruno Redondo. Later Copperhead made her first appearance in the mainstream DC Universe continuity in All-Star Batman, issue 2, created by Scott Snyder and John Romita Jr.

Note: There is a New 52 Copperhead, who is a male : Copperhead I.

Character Evolution

DC Rebirth / Prime Earth

After the start of the DC Rebirth initiative, Copperhead is introduced as an assassin for hire and a venom expert.

Major Story Arcs

My Own Worst Enemy

Batman and Two-Face are on a train, when Batman is attacked by Killer Croc, Amygdala and King Shark. Batman defeats the three villains, But he is then shot in the back with a poison arrow. He sees in front of him is Cheshire and behind him is Copperhead, who is the one that shot him with the arrow. Batman then sets off a series of bombs which blows up his train car. He and Two-Face escape from the two women.

Powers and Abilities

Copperhead is an excellent marksman. She also specializes in venom toxins.

Other Version

Batman: Arkham Unhinged

Copperhead's story continues from Batman: Arkham video games series.

Video Games

Batman: Arkham Origins

Copperhead appears in Batman: Arkham Origins as one of the eight assassins sent to kill Batman. She is sleek and agile South American hitwoman who uses poisons and sharp claws as weapons. She is seen sneaking up on Batman while he is interrogating Black Mask. She manages to poison him before he can fight her. The poison causes Batman to start hallucinating and he sees a group of Copperheads. When Batman beats them all, he gets the antidote and defeats the real Copperhead. He ties her up and locks her inside a truck.

Later when Batman updates the bat computer, it is revealed Copperhead is a member of a South American gang and that probably everyone in the gang is called "Copperhead".

She was voiced by Rosa Salazar. This version of the character was later imported to the comics.
